						<summary>

						<p>This records the renumeration of 48 <hi rend="italic">kalam</hi> of paddy by the king to the devotee, Palaviḷakkap-pichchar for tending the garden Vīrasōḻaṉ Tirunandāvaṉam. It is also stated that he was to get the above 48 <hi rend="italic">kalam</hi> from his share of taxes collected from Palloḍam <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Adirādhirāśanallūr. Sembiyan Uttaramantri figures as a signatory.</p>						

						</summary>
